---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = new Date("2026-06-18");
const dateLabel = new Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-US", {
  month: "long",
  day: "numeric",
  year: "numeric",
}).format(lastUpdated);
---

<Base
  title="Now"
  description="What Rafael Coelho is working on right now."
>
  <div class="container-page">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <p class="mb-2 font-mono text-[12px]" style="color: var(--color-accent);">/ now</p>
      <h1 class="mb-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight" style="color: var(--color-text);">
        What I'm working on
      </h1>
      <p class="font-mono text-[12px]" style="color: var(--color-text-dim);">
        Last updated · {dateLabel}
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-content">
      <h2>This week</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Shipping COELHO Nexus v1</strong> — Agentic RAG + GraphRAG search over YouTube
          transcripts. FastAPI + Qdrant + Neo4j + LangGraph on Oracle Free Tier.
        </li>
        <li>
          Wrapping up self-healing Playwright observability for the ingestion pipeline (Langfuse +
          OpenTelemetry).
        </li>
        <li>Migrating this site from Jekyll/al-folio to Astro 6 + Cloudflare Pages.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>This month</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Public launch of COELHO Nexus — first paying users in Brazil (Pix-first pricing), then
          LATAM and global tiers.
        </li>
        <li>
          Writing up the SOTA observability stack (Langfuse + OTEL + Grafana) we built for the
          Nexus pipeline.
        </li>
        <li>
          Talking to Senior AI/MLOps roles in the UAE (G42, Inception, Core42), Saudi Arabia, and
          Singapore.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        This is a
        <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">/now page</a>.
        A regularly updated snapshot of what I'm actually focused on right now — not what I'd like
        to be doing, not a roadmap, not aspirational. Built for the person who already knows me and
        wants to know what to ask about.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
